cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of finding a set of vertices in a graph that avoids a certain set of topological minors, which is a problem in graph theory. This makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) the most likely category. The fact that the problem is specifically studied on planar graphs suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another likely category. The use of parameterized algorithms suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible categories. Finally, the focus on algorithmic complexity and tractability suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible category as well.
